stylometry: Sensitivity analysis allows you to see how varying your input variables will cause a change in your output variables. It allows you to see how changing your input variables will have an effect on your outputs and therefore give you the best possible output so that you can get the optimum result to either minimize cost or maximize profit. It is important becuase it will lead you to make the best financial desicions when you have multiple choices to make requarding the inputs you could possible select and seeing how the multiple inputs will affect your outputs to make the best possible desicions.
